First, we need to find the symmetric difference of A and B (A △ B). The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets A or B but not in their intersection.

A = {1, 2, 3}
B = {2, 3, 4}

Intersection of A and B (A ∩ B) = {2, 3}

Now, we find the elements in either A or B but not in their intersection:

A △ B = {1, 4}

Next, we need to find the union of (A △ B) and B:

(A △ B) ∪ B = {1, 4} ∪ {2, 3, 4} = {1, 2, 3, 4}

So, (A △ B) ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4}.
